binding.p: Modern binding. Brown leather and marbled paper over wooden boards. , stamped in gold: HIERONYMI OPERA Msc.; stamped in gold: A 220.

history.provenance: Origin and early provenance unknown. In the 19th century, the manuscript belonged to Bernhard Rosenblad. It was purchased from him by G. J. R. Gordon.
history.acquisition: Purchased from G. J. R. Gordon by the Royal Library in .

supportDesc.foliation: : medieval foliation in brown ink, 1-159 (several numbers lost due to trimming).
supportDesc.condition: Wormholes with some damage to the text. Paper stained in places. : outer margins stained by liquid spill.

p.note: Frequent marginal notes in ink by one or more contemporary hands. These notes mainly consist of titles and summaries, and occasionally corrections. Many passages, e.g. on , are also marked with manicules and/or lines in the margin. At the beginning of some texts, references to Patrologia latina (Migne) in pencil by a modern hand.
Drawings in ink in the margin. Most of the drawings consist of small bust portraits in profile.

decoDesc.p: Main text in dark brown ink, rubrics in red, some capitals touched in red.
decoDesc.decoNote: , : Initials missing. space spanning 3-5 lines reserved for initials, sometimes marked with guide letters. : inital P, outlines in brown ink only. : opening plain initial I over 16 lines in red with flourishing in pink. : plain initials over 3-5 lines alternating in red and blue ink with flourishing in pink or red.
